file=AI & Agents/relay/operational/tool/relay-tool-requirements.md · r—t:relay — Tool Requirements=**This file specifies needs; it does not grant them.** Access is configured at deployment (operator/platform; Fleet Charter Rails 1–2 apply).\n · tb=\| Skill \| Needs \| Why \| · tb=\|---\|---\|---\| · tb=\| mcp-tool-registry \| file read/write (own assets/); script execution (registry_lint.py) \| maintain + validate the registry \| · tb=\| least-privilege-grants \| file read (other agents' SKILL.md files) \| verify skill-line citations \| · tb=\| egress-allowlist-authoring \| file read/write (own exports); handoff channel to quinn \| derive + deliver versioned allowlists \| · tb=\| integration-patterns \| file read (tool docs, registry) \| reliability reviews \| · r—t:relay — Tool Requirements=relay needs NO network access of its own and NO access to any external tool it registers — it is bookkeeping and authoring only. That asymmetry is deliberate.\n